data.description: Located in the sought-after Parkins Mill area you will find a private back yard oasis of mature landscaping surrounding a kidney shaped in ground SALT WATER POOL with SUNSET VIEWS over the CREEK flowing behind your property.  This is one of just 2 private pools in the subdivision.  The FENCED BACK YARD keeps your 2 or 4 legged loved ones safe.  A few steps away from the gourmet kitchen (featuring GAS COOKTOP / DOUBLE OVEN, Turkish travertine backsplash and PANTRY) is the HERB GARDEN to add fresh flavors to your culinary creations.  This home is great for entertainment, as it gives you multiple choices for dining - formal, casual or on the large SCREENED IN PORCH.   When location is everything, look no further.  This home is within walking distance to the SWAMP RABBIT TRAIL and GOWER PARK.  Craving a Frappuchino?  Starbucks is a short 0.25 mile walk away!  If access to the medical offices and the hospital system is important to you, access to MD 360 is a short 2 miles drive and Prisma’s Greenville Memorial Hospital is just 3.5 miles away.  Need a primary ENSUITE BEDROOM ON MAIN LEVEL for yourself or “in-laws”?  This home has you covered since there is are ensuite bedroom / bathroom combinations on both floors.  The owner’s suite on the upper level features a sitting area with a cozy gas log FIREPLACE that can be used for well deserved relaxation or as a work-at-home OFFICE area.  SOARING SMOOTH CEILINGS throughout allows for an abundance of natural light, yet this home is energy efficient, due to SPRAY FOAM INSULATION, GAS COOKTOP, and Low-E Argon filled double paned windows.  Need handy STORAGE?  Check out the raised storage system in the garage!  This real estate agent is jealous!  School area important to you?  This home is zoned for TOP RATED PUBLIC SCHOOLS:  Sara Collins, Beck, and J.L. Mann.  However, if you prefer private schools, CHRIST CHURCH EPISCOPAL SCHOOL and ST JOSEPH'S CATHOLIC SCHOOL are just 10 minute drive away.  Welcome home to the (in concept) perpetually “sunny” 4 Cloudless Circle!
